 backslashes become `\\\\`. Let me construct the final JSON output with the proper escape sequences, making sure the hints are accurate for each section. コード区分チェック\n\ns3 hints:\n- `TransactionAbnormalEnd` (exception class)\n- `DataRecord` (class name)\n- トレーラレコード精査\n- 総件数チェック\n- ゼロレコード制御\n- `allowZeroRecord`\n\nNow I'm putting together the complete JSON response. I need to verify that `allowZeroRecord` is included in the s3 hints since it's referenced in the code. For `official_doc_urls`, since the base URL is empty, I'll set it to an empty array following the pattern from other tasks.\n\nFor the sections content, I'm carefully formatting the code blocks and text, making sure to properly escape newlines and backslashes in the JSON strings.\n\nWriting s1 validation logic... Now I'm implementing the trailer record validation, checking that the previous record type is valid, verifying the total count matches the actual data record count, and handling the case where there are zero records but they're not allowed. Continuing to build the JSON structure with the index array, adding entries for each section of the batch processing logic with their corresponding hints and identifiers. Writing the header validation logic...\n\nNow for the data record handler, I need to increment the count and verify that the previous record was either a header or data record—if not, I'll throw an error for invalid file layout, then mark this as a data record before returning success.\n\nFor the trailer record validation, I'm checking that the previous record was a header or data record, confirming the total count matches the actual data record count, and ensuring we don't have zero records when that's not allowed—throwing an exit code 104 error if that condition fails. I'm running through a validation checklist to confirm the structure is correct—verifying that all section IDs match their references, content meets minimum length requirements, and the overall document integrity checks out.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24307,"cache_read_input_tokens":29889,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":24307,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2698c417-e15b-4b09-8d18-f6618d4b3155","uuid":"95777f5c-77a7-49ac-8bd1-9d1286bbb243"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_018PZ1G2jnig7kHZc5LJbhgB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Hm7Zi5RMX8HJKd22MZw6fq","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"id":"nablarch-batch-04_fileInputBatch--s1","title":"ファイルを入力とするバッチ","no_knowledge_content":false,"official_doc_urls":[],"index":[{"id":"s1","title":"ヘッダーレコードの精査処理","hints":["TransactionAbnormalEnd","BusinessDateUtil","DataRecord","ヘッダーレコード精査","業務日付チェック","ファイルレイアウト検証"]},{"id":"s2","title":"データレコードの精査処理","hints":["TransactionAbnormalEnd","DataRecord","データレコード精査","ファイルレイアウト検証","レコード区分チェック"]},{"id":"s3","title":"トレーラレコードの精査処理","hints":["TransactionAbnormalEnd","DataRecord","allowZeroRecord","トレーラレコード精査","総件数チェック","ゼロレコード制御"]}],"sections":{"s1":"以下のチェックを行う。\n\n- ヘッダーレコードは1レコード目であること（前レコードの値が非nullの場合は `INVALID_FILE_LAYOUT_FAILURE_CODE` でエラー終了）\n- ヘッダーレコードの日付フィールドと業務日付（`BusinessDateUtil.getDate()`）が一致すること\n\n```java\npublic Result doHeader(DataRecord inputData, ExecutionContext ctx) {\n    if (preRecordKbn != null) {\n        throw new TransactionAbnormalEnd(FILE_LAYOUT_ERROR_EXIT_CODE,\n                INVALID_FILE_LAYOUT_FAILURE_CODE, inputData.getRecordNumber());\n    }\n    String date = inputData.getString(\"date\");\n    String businessDate = BusinessDateUtil.getDate();\n    if (!businessDate.equals(date)) {\n        throw new TransactionAbnormalEnd(102,\n                HEADER_RECORD_ERROR_FAILURE_CODE, date, businessDate);\n    }\n    preRecordKbn = HEADER_RECORD;\n    return new Success();\n}\n```","s2":"前レコードのレコード区分は、ヘッダーレコードまたはデータレコードであること。そうでない場合は `TransactionAbnormalEnd` を送出して処理を終了する。\n\n```java\npublic Result doData(DataRecord inputData, ExecutionContext ctx) {\n    dataRecordCount++;\n    if (!HEADER_RECORD.equals(preRecordKbn) && !DATA_RECORD.equals(preRecordKbn)) {\n        throw new TransactionAbnormalEnd(FILE_LAYOUT_ERROR_EXIT_CODE,\n                INVALID_FILE_LAYOUT_FAILURE_CODE, inputData.getRecordNumber());\n    }\n    preRecordKbn = DATA_RECORD;\n    return new Success();\n}\n```","s3":"以下の精査処理を行う。\n\n- 前レコードのレコード区分は、データレコードまたはヘッダーレコードであること\n- 総件数項目（`totalCount`）の値がデータレコード数と一致すること\n- データレコード数が0かつ `allowZeroRecord` が `false` の場合はエラー（終了コード104）\n\n```java\npublic Result doTrailer(DataRecord inputData, ExecutionContext ctx) {\n    if (!DATA_RECORD.equals(preRecordKbn) && !HEADER_RECORD.equals(preRecordKbn)) {\n        throw new TransactionAbnormalEnd(FILE_LAYOUT_ERROR_EXIT_CODE,\n                INVALID_FILE_LAYOUT_FAILURE_CODE, inputData.getRecordNumber());\n    }\n    int totalCount = inputData.getBigDecimal(\"totalCount\").intValue();\n    if (dataRecordCount != totalCount) {\n        throw new TransactionAbnormalEnd(101,\n                TRAILER_RECORD_ERROR_FAILURE_CODE, totalCount, dataRecordCount);\n    }\n    if (dataRecordCount == 0 && !allowZeroRecord) {\n        throw new TransactionAbnormalEnd(104, \"NB11AA0106\");\n    }\n    preRecordKbn = TRAILER_RECORD;\n    return new Success();\n}\n```"}}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24307,"cache_read_input_tokens":29889,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":24307,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2698c417-e15b-4b09-8d18-f6618d4b3155","uuid":"e4acf41f-6b9e-42ee-b977-d8b06e481093"}
